40|$|This paper aims to add {{contribution}} to the <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> <b>investments</b> (from now on called “SRI”) research by examining {{the significance of this}} type of investment in terms of ethical or financial prior behaviour. Using the sample of European market of <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> <b>investments</b> funds, we first explore the SRI market dimension compared to the global data on SRI. We also investigate whether the ethical recognition is more important rather than the financial performance. Applied to the European social <b>responsible</b> <b>investment</b> fund market, the paper investigates the difference between these two aspects of behaviour and underlies the importance of <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> <b>investments</b> in promoting a sustainable development...|$|R
