40|$|This study formulates a two-factor {{empirical}} model under the intertemporal CAPM framework {{to evaluate the}} cross-sectional implications of <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> <b>investments</b> in the US equity market. Our results show that <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> <b>investments</b> have no asset pricing impact on the US market. We argue that this ‘no financial impact’ finding indicates that investors will not be disadvantaged financially by investing in <b>socially</b> <b>responsible</b> funds or corporations...|$|R
